      {
        "id": 4558695,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-01-19T13:09:22.121Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Pierre-Yves does indeed own the vineyards he works with in En Remilly - 2/3 of a hectare in three parcels.</p>\n<p>In 2021, En Remilly was heavily frosted, and they produced only four barrels (13hl/ha). I hadn\u2019t seen the label but I guess they decided to give it a special one given the tiny quantity.</p>",
