        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/67e7ee/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-01-19T13:14:59.134Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Interesting, as I bought this cuvee also in 2017, now the 2021 is being offered. 2017 wasn\u2019t a particularly frosty year. And he does indeed produce a straightforward En Remilly in 2017 with a rather hefty pricetag\u2026$275 on Winesearcher.</p>\n<p>Thanks for the information about his holdings! You are the best. Perhaps this is a proverbial \u201cStump the Chumps\u201d question? <img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/images/emoji/unicode/laughing.png?v=12\" title=\":laughing:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":laughing:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
